{
  "id": "feature-perf-009-server-caching-compression",
  "title": "Server-Side Feature Caching and HTTP Compression",
  "category": "Performance",
  "description": "## Problem\nThe Express server lacks HTTP compression middleware and has no in-memory caching for frequently-accessed data. Every API call to list features reads ALL feature JSON files from disk. Large JSON responses (feature lists, agent output) are sent uncompressed. Git diff/status operations spawn fresh child processes on every call.\n\n## Current Behavior\n\n### No HTTP Compression - `apps/server/src/index.ts` (lines 141-200):\nNo `compression` middleware. JSON responses for feature lists with descriptions, agent output markdown (can be 100KB+), and settings responses are all sent uncompressed.\n\n### No Feature Caching - `apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts`:\n- `getAll()` (lines 199-258): Reads ALL feature directories and parses ALL JSON files on every call\n- `getAllSummaries()` (lines 265-371): Same pattern, reads all features from disk\n- `findByTitle()` / `findDuplicateTitle()` (lines 386-434): Calls `getAll()` which loads ALL features just to find one by title\n- With 50+ features, each poll reads 50+ JSON files from disk\n\n### No Git Diff Caching - `libs/git-utils/src/diff.ts` (lines 265-276):\n```typescript\nconst { stdout: diff } = await execAsync('git diff HEAD', { cwd: repoPath, maxBuffer: 10 * 1024 * 1024 });\nconst { stdout: status } = await execAsync('git status --porcelain', { cwd: repoPath });\n```\nEvery call spawns 2 child processes. Auto-mode and worktree panel poll frequently.\n\n### Only Image Endpoint Has Cache Headers:\n`apps/server/src/routes/fs/routes/image.ts` (line 59): `Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600` - but only for images.\n\n## Required Changes\n\n### 1. Add HTTP Compression Middleware\n- Install `compression` npm package\n- Add `app.use(compression())` in `apps/server/src/index.ts` after `cookieParser()` (after line 200)\n- This will gzip/brotli all JSON responses automatically\n\n### 2. Add Feature List TTL Cache\n- In `apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts`:\n  - Add a simple in-memory cache with 5-10 second TTL for `getAll()` results\n  - Key by `projectPath`\n  - Invalidate on create/update/delete operations (the `save()`, `create()`, `delete()` methods)\n  - Add a feature title index for O(1) lookups instead of scanning all features\n\n### 3. Add Git Diff/Status Caching\n- In `libs/git-utils/src/diff.ts`:\n  - Add a short TTL cache (3-5 seconds) for `getGitRepositoryDiffs()` results\n  - Key by `repoPath`\n  - Prevents redundant process spawning during rapid polling\n\n### 4. Add Cache-Control Headers for Stable Endpoints\n- `/api/models` - model list rarely changes, cache for 5 minutes\n- `/api/setup/status` - status checks, cache for 30 seconds\n- Static assets served by Express should have long cache headers\n\n### 5. Add Lightweight Running-Features Endpoint\n- Create `GET /api/features/running` that returns only `{count, features: [{id, title, status}]}`\n- Much lighter than the full `getAll()` used by `use-running-agents.ts`\n\n## Pattern to Follow (Feature Cache)\n```typescript\n// apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts\nclass FeatureCache {\n  private cache = new Map<string, { features: Feature[]; timestamp: number }>();\n  private readonly TTL_MS = 5000; // 5 seconds\n\n  get(projectPath: string): Feature[] | null {\n    const entry = this.cache.get(projectPath);\n    if (!entry) return null;\n    if (Date.now() - entry.timestamp > this.TTL_MS) {\n      this.cache.delete(projectPath);\n      return null;\n    }\n    return entry.features;\n  }\n\n  set(projectPath: string, features: Feature[]) {\n    this.cache.set(projectPath, { features, timestamp: Date.now() });\n  }\n\n  invalidate(projectPath: string) {\n    this.cache.delete(projectPath);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Files to Modify\n- `apps/server/package.json` - Add `compression` dependency\n- `apps/server/src/index.ts` - Add compression middleware, add cache headers\n- `apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts` - Add feature caching with TTL, title index\n- `libs/git-utils/src/diff.ts` - Add git diff/status caching\n- `apps/server/src/routes/features/` - Add lightweight `/api/features/running` endpoint\n\n## Expected Impact\n- HTTP responses 60-80% smaller with compression (gzip)\n- Feature list API calls 90% faster when cached (memory vs disk)\n- Git operations reduced by 80% during rapid polling\n- Reduced disk I/O and child process spawning\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Response headers include `Content-Encoding: gzip` (verify in Network tab)\n- Feature list calls return cached data within TTL (verify with server logs showing cache hit/miss)\n- Git diff operations are cached for 3-5 seconds (verify with process monitoring)\n- `findByTitle` is O(1) instead of O(n)\n- Cache invalidates correctly on feature create/update/delete\n- `/api/features/running` endpoint returns lightweight data\n\n## Reference\n- `apps/server/src/services/codex-model-cache-service.ts` - Good example of TTL caching with disk persistence\n- `apps/server/src/routes/github/routes/validation-common.ts` (lines 28-43, 129-143) - TTL cache pattern with cleanup",
