    "content": "I'll start by exploring the codebase to understand the existing structure, then generate a comprehensive specification.\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:44:15.373Z] 🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore server caching structure\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\",\n  \"prompt\": \"Explore the following files thoroughly and report their contents/structure:\\n\\n1. `apps/server/src/index.ts` - Focus on middleware setup (lines 140-210), how Express app is configured\\n2. `apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts` - Focus on getAll(), getAllSummaries(), findByTitle(), findDuplicateTitle(), save(), create(), delete() methods\\n3. `libs/git-utils/src/diff.ts` - Focus on getGitRepositoryDiffs() and how git diff/status commands are spawned\\n4. `apps/server/src/routes/features/` - All route files, especially index.ts\\n5. `apps/server/src/services/codex-model-cache-service.ts` - TTL caching pattern example\\n6. `apps/server/src/routes/github/routes/validation-common.ts` - TTL cache pattern (lines 28-43, 129-143)\\n7. `apps/server/package.json` - Current dependencies\\n8. `apps/server/src/routes/fs/routes/image.ts` - Cache-Control header pattern (around line 59)\\n\\nFor each file, report the key structures, function signatures, and line numbers for important sections. Be very thorough - I need exact line numbers and code patterns.\",\n  \"run_in_background\": true\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:44:33.037Z] 🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore running agents hooks\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\",\n  \"prompt\": \"Find and explore these files to understand the running agents pattern:\\n\\n1. `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts` - How does the UI poll for running agents? What API endpoint does it call? What data does it need?\\n2. `apps/server/src/routes/features/routes/list-summaries.ts` - This is an untracked new file, read it if it exists\\n3. `apps/server/src/routes/features/routes/summaries.ts` - This is an untracked new file, read it if it exists\\n4. Any route files in `apps/server/src/routes/features/routes/` - list all of them\\n5. `apps/server/src/routes/models.ts` or similar - find the /api/models endpoint\\n6. `apps/server/src/routes/setup/` - find the /api/setup/status endpoint\\n7. `libs/git-utils/src/index.ts` - What's exported from git-utils?\\n\\nReport file contents, function signatures, line numbers for key sections.\",\n  \"run_in_background\": true\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:44:37.229Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"ae7dff5\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 30000\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:45:50.647Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"a20c912\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 30000\n}\nLet me read the key files directly while waiting for the agents.\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:46:46.659Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\index.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:46:47.154Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\services\\\\feature-loader.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:46:47.666Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\libs\\\\git-utils\\\\src\\\\diff.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:47:45.960Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"a20c912\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 30000\n}\nLet me read the remaining key files directly:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:48:22.581Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\features\\\\index.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:48:22.907Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\running-agents\\\\index.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:48:23.293Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\\\\use-running-agents.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:48:23.963Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\github\\\\routes\\\\validation-common.ts\"\n}\nNow let me read the remaining critical files:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:49:22.226Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\package.json\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:49:24.139Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\models\\\\index.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:49:24.678Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\setup\\\\index.ts\"\n}\nNow let me also check the existing feature list route and the running agents route handler:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:50:38.300Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\features\\\\routes\\\\list.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:50:40.188Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\running-agents\\\\routes\\\\index.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:50:40.560Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\fs\\\\routes\\\\image.ts\"\n}\nNow I have all the context I need. Let me generate the specification.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\nThe Express server sends all JSON responses uncompressed, reads all feature JSON files from disk on every API call, and spawns fresh child processes for git diff/status on every invocation. With 50+ features, this creates significant disk I/O, process spawning overhead, and bandwidth waste that degrades responsiveness as projects scale.\n\n## 2. User Story\n\nAs a developer using Automaker, I want the server to compress HTTP responses, cache frequently-accessed feature data in memory, and avoid redundant git operations, so that the UI loads faster and the server uses fewer system resources.\n\n## 3. Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Happy Path\n- **GIVEN** the server is running, **WHEN** a client requests `/api/features/list`, **THEN** the response includes `Content-Encoding: gzip` or `br` header and the payload is compressed.\n- **GIVEN** features have been loaded for a project within the last 5 seconds, **WHEN** another `/api/features/list` call is made for the same project, **THEN** the server returns cached data without reading from disk (cache hit logged).\n- **GIVEN** a feature is created/updated/deleted, **WHEN** the next list call occurs, **THEN** fresh data is returned (cache was invalidated).\n- **GIVEN** git diff was fetched for a repo within the last 3 seconds, **WHEN** another `getGitRepositoryDiffs()` call is made for the same repo, **THEN** cached results are returned without spawning child processes.\n- **GIVEN** the `findByTitle()` method is called, **WHEN** features are cached, **THEN** the lookup is O(1) via the title index.\n\n### Edge Cases\n- **GIVEN** the cache TTL expires, **WHEN** the next request comes in, **THEN** data is freshly loaded from disk and re-cached.\n- **GIVEN** two concurrent requests arrive for the same uncached project, **WHEN** both trigger loads, **THEN** only one disk read occurs (no thundering herd).\n- **GIVEN** a cache entry exists for project A, **WHEN** project B features are requested, **THEN** project B loads from disk (per-project keying).\n\n### Error Handling\n- **GIVEN** the cache is populated but the underlying disk read fails on refresh, **WHEN** the stale cache is available, **THEN** the system gracefully falls through to error handling (does not serve stale data for mutating operations).\n\n## 4. Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Affected Files | `apps/server/package.json`, `apps/server/src/index.ts`, `apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts`, `libs/git-utils/src/diff.ts`, `apps/server/src/routes/features/index.ts`, `apps/server/src/routes/features/routes/running.ts` (new) |\n| Dependencies | `compression` npm package (new) |\n| Constraints | Cache TTL must be short (3-10s) to avoid stale data; git-utils is a shared library so changes must be backwards-compatible |\n| Patterns to Follow | TTL cache pattern from `validation-common.ts`, `codex-model-cache-service.ts`; Cache-Control pattern from `image.ts` line 59 |\n\n## 5. Non-Goals\n\n- Persistent disk-based caching (only in-memory TTL cache)\n- Redis or external cache stores\n- HTTP ETag or conditional request support\n- Caching of individual feature reads (`get()` by ID)\n- WebSocket message compression (separate concern)\n- Changing the UI polling intervals\n\n## 6. Implementation Tasks\n\n```tasks\n## Phase 1: HTTP Compression\n- [ ] T001: Install `compression` npm package | File: apps/server/package.json\n- [ ] T002: Add compression middleware after cookieParser() in Express setup | File: apps/server/src/index.ts\n\n## Phase 2: Feature List TTL Cache\n- [ ] T003: Add FeatureCache class with TTL, per-project keying, and title index to FeatureLoader | File: apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts\n- [ ] T004: Integrate cache into getAll(), getAllSummaries(), getAllListSummaries() methods | File: apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts\n- [ ] T005: Add cache invalidation to create(), update(), delete() methods | File: apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts\n- [ ] T006: Optimize findByTitle() and findDuplicateTitle() to use title index from cache | File: apps/server/src/services/feature-loader.ts\n\n## Phase 3: Git Diff/Status Caching\n- [ ] T007: Add TTL cache (3-5s) to getGitRepositoryDiffs() keyed by repoPath | File: libs/git-utils/src/diff.ts\n\n## Phase 4: Cache-Control Headers\n- [ ] T008: Add Cache-Control headers to /api/models routes (5 min) | File: apps/server/src/routes/models/index.ts\n\n## Phase 5: Lightweight Running-Features Endpoint\n- [ ] T009: Create GET /api/features/running endpoint returning minimal running feature data | File: apps/server/src/routes/features/routes/running.ts\n- [ ] T010: Register the new running endpoint in features router | File: apps/server/src/routes/features/index.ts\n```\n\n## 7. Success Metrics\n\n| Metric | Target |\n|--------|--------|\n| Response `Content-Encoding` header | Present as `gzip` or `br` on JSON responses |\n| Feature list cache hit rate | >80% during normal polling (5s TTL vs 2-3s poll intervals) |\n| `findByTitle()` complexity | O(1) map lookup instead of O(n) scan |\n| Git diff redundant spawns | Eliminated within 3s windows |\n| `/api/features/running` payload size | <1KB vs full feature list |\n| Server unit tests | All existing tests pass |\n\n## 8. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Stale cache data served after mutation | Cache is invalidated immediately on create/update/delete calls within the same FeatureLoader instance |\n| Memory growth from cache | TTL is short (3-10s); entries evict automatically; Map keyed by project path has bounded cardinality |\n| Compression CPU overhead | `compression` package uses native zlib; threshold defaults skip small responses; only compresses compressible content types |\n| Git cache hiding real changes | 3-second TTL is short enough that changes appear quickly; cache is only for the diff output, not for mutation operations |\n| Breaking `@automaker/git-utils` consumers | Cache is internal to the function; the export signature is unchanged |\n\n---",
